<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="endo_hormones_digt"><title>tutor</title><page><question id="q1"><body>Which of the following accurately describes hormones?</body><multiple_choice select="single" shuffle="true"><choice value="A">Elicit a body-wide response from all cell types</choice><choice value="B">Circulate indefinitely in the body</choice><choice value="C">Are chemical messengers</choice><choice value="D">Are neural messengers</choice></multiple_choice><part id="i9ae6da2792d24355ba9d22e69b475b4e"><skillref idref="endo_hormones_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Hormones can only elicit responses from target cells.</feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Hormones will degrade or eventually will be eliminated.</feedback></response><response match="C" score="10"><feedback>Correct. Hormones are chemical messengers.</feedback></response><response match="D" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Neural messages are carried through electrical impulses.</feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
